t of Education (IDOE) page listed below, then click on Family Resources.Â  These resources have been reviewed by IDOE staff.<br><br><a href="https://www.mobymax.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" onclick="window.open(this.href,'','scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes,location=yes,menubar=yes,status=yes,toolbar=yes,left=0,top=0');return false;"></a><a href="https://www.doe.in.gov/elearning/2020-covid-19-remote-learning?utm_content=&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_name=&amp;utm_source=govdelivery&amp;utm_term=" onclick="window.open(this.href,'','scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes,location=yes,menubar=yes,status=yes,toolbar=yes,left=0,top=0');return false;">Indiana Department of Education COVID-19 Remote Learning</a><br><br><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Archived Parent Letters</strong></span><br><br><a href="/images/Parent_Letter_-_3-25-20.pdf">Parent Letter March 25, 2020</a>Â - This letter describes additional information regarding e-learning, meal service, and reduced school office hours.<br><br><a href="/images/Parent_Letter_-_3-20-20.pdf">Parent Letter March 20, 2020Â </a>- This letter describes the various plans to continue the continuity of instruction, learning, and food services for our students.<br><br><a href="/images/Parent_Letter_-_3-13-20.pdf">Parent Letter March 13, 2020</a>Â - This letter describes additional details of school closure from Saturday, March 14th - Sunday, March 29th.Â  In addition, it recommends parents begin making childcare arrangements now for the possible extended closure of school beginning Monday, March 30th.<br><br><a href="/images/Parent_Letter_-_3-12-20.pdf">Parent Letter March 12, 2020</a>Â - This letter announces the closure of school for Monday, March 16th and Tuesday, March 17th.<br><br><a href="/images/Parent_Letter_-_03-10-20.pdf">Parent Letter March 10, 2020</a>Â - This letter describes the initial plans for combatting the spread of COVID-19 and an overview of preparedness plans. 
	
	
	
